1
00:02:15,666 --> 00:02:16,875
Oh.

2
00:02:16,958 --> 00:02:18,666
Thank you, Kodaka;
that was really nice of you.

3
00:02:18,750 --> 00:02:20,500
Now if you'll excuse me.

4
00:02:20,583 --> 00:02:22,583
Y'know what; hold on a sec.

5
00:02:22,666 --> 00:02:23,791
Let me get one.

6
00:02:23,875 --> 00:02:25,291
I appreciate that, Kodaka.

7
00:02:25,375 --> 00:02:26,750
You're very welcome, Aoi.

8
00:02:26,833 --> 00:02:28,458
I guess you can go ahead
and follow me this way

9
00:02:28,541 --> 00:02:29,833
if you want to.

10
00:02:33,541 --> 00:02:34,791
[KODAKA]
Carrying two boxes this heavy

11
00:02:34,875 --> 00:02:37,250
at once makes it seem like
you want them to fall.

12
00:02:37,333 --> 00:02:39,125
[AOI] I don't; I'm just
trying to make up time

13
00:02:39,208 --> 00:02:41,958
on my student council work
since I skipped it for a week.

14
00:02:42,041 --> 00:02:43,791
[KODAKA]
You skipped for a week?

15
00:02:47,208 --> 00:02:49,041
[KODAKA]
Hey, do you mind telling me

16
00:02:49,125 --> 00:02:51,875
why you were so set on
destroying the Neighbors Club?

17
00:02:53,083 --> 00:02:55,125
Because Sena is
exceptionally gifted.

18
00:02:55,208 --> 00:02:57,833
And she should be somewhere
appropriate for her gifts.

19
00:02:57,916 --> 00:02:59,541
What do you mean
somewhere appropriate?

20
00:02:59,625 --> 00:03:00,750
Face it.

21
00:03:00,833 --> 00:03:02,708
Sena Kashiwazaki is
unbelievably talented

22
00:03:02,791 --> 00:03:04,833
and needed a better way
to make use of those talents.

23
00:03:04,916 --> 00:03:06,750
Your club was just
a waste of her time.

24
00:03:06,833 --> 00:03:08,083
Wow.

25
00:03:08,166 --> 00:03:09,833
So then, you tried to
disband the Neighbors Club

26
00:03:09,916 --> 00:03:11,666
for the sake of your
so-called mortal enemy?

27
00:03:11,750 --> 00:03:13,250
Yes.

28
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:16,458
If you say so.

29
00:03:18,708 --> 00:03:20,250
[KODAKA]
I guess she has a point.

30
00:03:20,333 --> 00:03:23,833
Sena would be an asset to
any club she decided to join.

31
00:03:23,916 --> 00:03:25,583
It's not just her, either.

32
00:03:25,666 --> 00:03:29,166
Yozora and Rika have that super
smart thing going on for them.

33
00:03:29,250 --> 00:03:32,583
And then you have Yukimura and
Kobato, who are both popular.

34
00:03:32,666 --> 00:03:34,166
Maybe Aoi's right.

35
00:03:34,250 --> 00:03:36,583
Maybe there's really no point to
even having the Neighbors Club.

36
00:03:36,666 --> 00:03:38,125
[AOI]
No, I'm just kidding.

37
00:03:38,208 --> 00:03:39,083
You what?

38
00:03:39,166 --> 00:03:40,500
I don't like Sena.

39
00:03:40,583 --> 00:03:42,333
She gets everything her
little heart desires, so I just

40
00:03:42,416 --> 00:03:45,291
wanted her to realize she
might lose something one day.

41
00:03:45,375 --> 00:03:48,125
So in other words,
I'm wicked jealous of her.

42
00:03:48,208 --> 00:03:49,666
Well, the funny thing
is you're wrong;

43
00:03:49,750 --> 00:03:50,958
she doesn't have everything.

44
00:03:51,041 --> 00:03:51,750
Yeah?

45
00:03:51,833 --> 00:03:53,083
What doesn't she have?

46
00:03:53,166 --> 00:03:54,416
She doesn't have friends.

47
00:03:55,791 --> 00:03:57,208
Jeez, are you okay?

48
00:03:57,291 --> 00:04:00,666
[AOI laughing]

49
00:04:00,750 --> 00:04:02,208
[KODAKA]
Why are you laughing?

50
00:04:02,291 --> 00:04:04,458
I forgot you have such
a great sense of humor.

51
00:04:04,541 --> 00:04:06,291
You're hilarious,
you know that?

52
00:04:06,375 --> 00:04:08,708
I'm not falling for it, though;
there's not a single person

53
00:04:08,791 --> 00:04:11,375
in the whole world
who doesn't have friends.

54
00:04:11,458 --> 00:04:13,333
[AOI]
I wouldn't be so sure.

55
00:04:13,416 --> 00:04:14,500
It was really sweet of you

56
00:04:14,583 --> 00:04:16,583
to try and cheer me up
after what I did.

57
00:04:16,666 --> 00:04:18,250
Thank you again, Kodaka.

58
00:04:25,083 --> 00:04:27,625
[AOI]
Almost--There.

59
00:04:27,708 --> 00:04:28,666
You were a big help.

60
00:04:28,750 --> 00:04:30,208
I couldn't have
done it without you.

61
00:04:30,291 --> 00:04:31,541
You still have more, yeah?

62
00:04:31,625 --> 00:04:32,666
I can help you with those.

63
00:04:32,750 --> 00:04:35,000
[AOI]
No, I can't ask you to do that.

64
00:04:35,083 --> 00:04:37,750
[KODAKA] This stuff got piled up
because of the Neighbors Club.

65
00:04:37,833 --> 00:04:40,708
So I'm partly to blame;
I can't not help you.

66
00:04:40,791 --> 00:04:43,166
Don't you need to go meet
with that club, though?

67
00:04:43,250 --> 00:04:46,083
Well, we're not really big on
planning activities every day.

68
00:04:46,166 --> 00:04:49,833
So if we have other stuff to
do first, it's not a big deal.

69
00:04:49,916 --> 00:04:52,666
[KODAKA] Why do I feel like
I have to make excuses?

70
00:04:52,750 --> 00:04:54,125
Weird.

71
00:04:57,583 --> 00:04:59,541
[KODAKA] Well on the bright
side, we made it halfway.

72
00:04:59,625 --> 00:05:00,666
[AOI]
I guess so.

73
00:05:00,750 --> 00:05:02,458
[GIRL laughing]

74
00:05:02,541 --> 00:05:04,875
[HINATA] Well, you two seem
to be working well together.

75
00:05:04,958 --> 00:05:06,083
[AOI]
Hinata.

76
00:05:06,166 --> 00:05:07,375
What did you come out here for?

77
00:05:07,458 --> 00:05:09,583
I heard some extremely
nice individual started

78
00:05:09,666 --> 00:05:10,958
helping you with your chores.

79
00:05:11,041 --> 00:05:13,166
I thought I'd come check
on you and thank him myself.

80
00:05:13,250 --> 00:05:13,833
Oh.

81
00:05:13,916 --> 00:05:15,000
Uh, hello.

82
00:05:15,083 --> 00:05:17,125
I'm Kodaka Hasegawa
from class Two-Five.

83
00:05:17,208 --> 00:05:18,083
Oh yeah.

84
00:05:18,166 --> 00:05:19,375
Yeah, it's totally you.

85
00:05:19,458 --> 00:05:21,125
[AOI]
Wait, you know who he is?

86
00:05:21,208 --> 00:05:21,666
Nope.

87
00:05:21,750 --> 00:05:22,916
No clue.

88
00:05:23,000 --> 00:05:24,666
[AOI] Then what the heck
was that reaction about?

89
00:05:24,750 --> 00:05:25,291
I dunno.

90
00:05:25,375 --> 00:05:26,333
Call it a whim.

91
00:05:28,333 --> 00:05:30,541
I'm Hinata,
the student council president.

92
00:05:30,625 --> 00:05:32,083
It's nice to meet you.

93
00:05:32,166 --> 00:05:32,833
Yeah.

94
00:05:32,916 --> 00:05:34,291
Cool.

95
00:05:44,458 --> 00:05:46,875
Hey, I was wondering,
why are you helping Aoi?

96
00:05:46,958 --> 00:05:48,208
This is a lot of work.

97
00:05:48,291 --> 00:05:50,583
You guys must be like
dating or something, yeah?

98
00:05:50,666 --> 00:05:51,208
No!

99
00:05:51,291 --> 00:05:52,541
We're not dating.

100
00:05:52,625 --> 00:05:55,166
Besides, Kodaka probably
already has a girlfriend.

101
00:05:55,250 --> 00:05:56,083
Do you have a girlfriend?

102
00:05:56,166 --> 00:05:57,250
Um, no.

103
00:05:57,333 --> 00:05:58,666
Come on, you're telling me

104
00:05:58,750 --> 00:06:01,250
that you're not dating anyone
from the Neighbors Club?

105
00:06:01,333 --> 00:06:02,583
No, I am not.

106
00:06:02,666 --> 00:06:05,166
It just isn't like that
with them, okay.

107
00:06:05,250 --> 00:06:05,875
[AOI]
Hm.

108
00:06:05,958 --> 00:06:07,166
Prob'ly for the best.

109
00:06:07,250 --> 00:06:08,250
[KODAKA]
What do you mean?

110
00:06:08,333 --> 00:06:09,666
What's for the best?

111
00:06:09,750 --> 00:06:11,458
Well, if you think about it,
you're the only boy

112
00:06:11,541 --> 00:06:13,958
in the whole club, so
you're surrounded by girls.

113
00:06:14,041 --> 00:06:15,291
If you dated one of them,

114
00:06:15,375 --> 00:06:19,166
the whole atmosphere
would get like way awkward.

115
00:06:19,250 --> 00:06:20,166
Yeah.

116
00:06:20,250 --> 00:06:21,750
That's for sure.

117
00:06:21,833 --> 00:06:23,125
So.

118
00:06:23,208 --> 00:06:24,833
If you're not her boyfriend,
why are you helping out?

119
00:06:24,916 --> 00:06:26,583
Because he happens to be
one of those guys who

120
00:06:26,666 --> 00:06:29,166
comes to the rescue when
he sees someone in trouble.

121
00:06:29,250 --> 00:06:29,958
Oh my.

122
00:06:30,041 --> 00:06:32,000
Well isn't that fancy.

123
00:06:34,375 --> 00:06:36,333
[HINATA]
Keep up the good work, kid!

124
00:06:38,250 --> 00:06:40,333
[KODAKA]
Okay, I think that's it.

125
00:06:43,083 --> 00:06:45,541
For the last time,
thanks so much for your help.

126
00:06:45,625 --> 00:06:47,708
Don't worry about it;
it's not a problem.

127
00:06:47,791 --> 00:06:49,041
See ya later.

128
00:06:49,916 --> 00:06:51,458
Oh hey, uh Kodaka.

129
00:06:51,541 --> 00:06:52,500
Yeah?

130
00:06:52,583 --> 00:06:54,000
You seem like
you're a cool guy.

131
00:06:54,083 --> 00:06:56,583
Wanna join the
student council with us?

132
00:06:56,666 --> 00:06:58,416
We just lost our general
affairs person, so we're

133
00:06:58,500 --> 00:07:01,333
looking for a replacement,
if you're interested.

134
00:07:01,416 --> 00:07:03,541
You should definitely join;
it'll be a ton of fun;

135
00:07:03,625 --> 00:07:04,375
I promise.

136
00:07:04,458 --> 00:07:05,541
Really?

137
00:07:05,625 --> 00:07:06,958
I'm surprised you'd
wanna work with me.

138
00:07:07,041 --> 00:07:08,916
Actually, the council only
has girls on it right now.

139
00:07:09,000 --> 00:07:11,458
I think it would be nice
for us to have a guy around.

140
00:07:11,541 --> 00:07:14,625
Honestly, Kodaka, you would be
perfect on the student council.

141
00:07:14,708 --> 00:07:16,041
I don't know.

142
00:07:16,125 --> 00:07:18,375
Haven't you heard the way
people talk about me?

143
00:07:18,458 --> 00:07:20,583
I don't want to
bring you guys down.

144
00:07:20,666 --> 00:07:22,166
I don't get it.

145
00:07:22,250 --> 00:07:25,541
What's wrong with a super-cool,
bad-boy chic, real life haver?

146
00:07:25,625 --> 00:07:26,875
Yeah, thank you,

147
00:07:26,958 --> 00:07:28,541
but you're the only one
who thinks that about me.

148
00:07:28,625 --> 00:07:30,625
See, most people
don't think I'm bad-boy chic,

149
00:07:30,708 --> 00:07:32,166
they assume I'm just bad.

150
00:07:32,250 --> 00:07:34,625
I get called a delinquent
and all sorts of mean things.

151
00:07:34,708 --> 00:07:36,833
It's cuz I have weird hair
and a grumpy face.

152
00:07:39,875 --> 00:07:41,375
[HINATA]
That's true.

153
00:07:41,458 --> 00:07:44,250
Your hair does get attention,
and you have evil looking eyes.

154
00:07:44,333 --> 00:07:45,416
There, you see?

155
00:07:45,500 --> 00:07:46,791
Putting me on the
student council would

156
00:07:46,875 --> 00:07:48,666
wreck your reputation,
and I don't want to do that.

157
00:07:48,750 --> 00:07:50,458
Only fools
judge on appearances,

158
00:07:50,541 --> 00:07:53,041
and I simply don't
care what fools think.

159
00:07:53,125 --> 00:07:56,250
Are you gonna let idiots decide
what you can and can't do?

160
00:07:58,416 --> 00:07:59,250
What's the matter, Kodaka?

161
00:07:59,333 --> 00:08:00,875
You look a little dazed.

162
00:08:00,958 --> 00:08:01,583
[KODAKA]
No.

163
00:08:01,666 --> 00:08:02,750
I mean, yes; I'm fine.

164
00:08:02,833 --> 00:08:03,541
Good to hear.

165
00:08:03,625 --> 00:08:05,666
So, are you gonna join?

166
00:08:07,125 --> 00:08:07,625
No.

167
00:08:07,708 --> 00:08:08,708
No, I'm sorry.

168
00:08:08,791 --> 00:08:10,166
I think the
student council might be

169
00:08:10,250 --> 00:08:11,875
a little too much for me.

170
00:08:11,958 --> 00:08:14,291
But, if all you need is more
manual labor, just let me know.

171
00:08:14,375 --> 00:08:17,083
I'd be happy to help out
whenever and wherever I can.

172
00:08:17,166 --> 00:08:18,708
Plus, I'm almost always free.

173
00:08:18,791 --> 00:08:19,958
Really?

174
00:08:20,041 --> 00:08:21,416
The library asked for us
to help with a project,

175
00:08:21,500 --> 00:08:22,833
so if you'd like
to come by tomorrow,

176
00:08:22,916 --> 00:08:23,833
that would be so great.

177
00:08:23,916 --> 00:08:24,541
Sure.

178
00:08:24,625 --> 00:08:26,333
Count on me to be there.

179
00:08:26,416 --> 00:08:27,916
That's the perfect answer!

180
00:08:29,166 --> 00:08:30,458
[KODAKA]
A week went by so fast,

181
00:08:30,541 --> 00:08:34,083
I barely even realized
what was happening.

182
00:08:34,166 --> 00:08:37,875
I ended up helping the student
council pretty much every day.

183
00:08:37,958 --> 00:08:39,708
It's kind of funny.

184
00:08:39,791 --> 00:08:42,208
All the kids at school think
Hinata is like a god for

185
00:08:42,291 --> 00:08:45,166
"getting that punk in line".

186
00:08:45,250 --> 00:08:48,625
She's getting even
more popular than before.

187
00:08:48,708 --> 00:08:50,916
My reputation's
the same, though.

188
00:08:51,000 --> 00:08:53,375
No surprise, there.

189
00:08:53,458 --> 00:08:56,166
I haven't set foot into
our clubroom since then.

190
00:08:56,250 --> 00:08:57,375
Don't get me wrong,

191
00:08:57,458 --> 00:08:59,375
the Neighbors Club
still means a lot to me.

192
00:08:59,458 --> 00:09:03,208
But after running out on them
like that, I couldn't go back.

193
00:09:03,291 --> 00:09:05,916
I don't know why;
I just couldn't.

194
00:09:12,208 --> 00:09:13,875
[YUKIMURA]
Look who I finally found.

195
00:09:19,541 --> 00:09:20,916
[KODAKA]
Yukimura.

196
00:09:22,291 --> 00:09:23,708
Big Brother.

197
00:09:29,875 --> 00:09:30,583
[KODAKA]
Oh.

198
00:09:30,666 --> 00:09:31,875
Hey, Yukimura.

199
00:09:31,958 --> 00:09:33,000
What's up?

200
00:09:33,083 --> 00:09:35,083
I heard a despicable
gang captured you,

201
00:09:35,166 --> 00:09:37,625
and that they were forcing
you to do manual labor.

202
00:09:37,708 --> 00:09:39,166
So I have come to your rescue.

203
00:09:39,250 --> 00:09:40,875
You know, that's
really rude to say.

204
00:09:40,958 --> 00:09:42,583
Kodaka's helping us
because he's nice,

205
00:09:42,666 --> 00:09:44,583
and that's all there is to it.

206
00:09:44,666 --> 00:09:45,416
Seriously?

207
00:09:45,500 --> 00:09:47,208
Is that the truth, Brother?

208
00:09:47,291 --> 00:09:48,541
Yeah.

209
00:09:48,625 --> 00:09:50,375
[YUKIMURA] In that case,
I shall help out as well.

210
00:09:50,458 --> 00:09:51,291
[AOI]
No, thanks!

211
00:09:51,375 --> 00:09:53,125
And besides, why would you?

212
00:09:53,208 --> 00:09:54,875
Aren't you the one
who wanted to poison me?

213
00:09:54,958 --> 00:09:56,083
I am.

214
00:09:56,166 --> 00:09:57,875
Why are you wearing
a boys' uniform, anyway?

215
00:09:57,958 --> 00:09:59,875
I'm wearing this uniform
because I am endeavoring

216
00:09:59,958 --> 00:10:00,958
to become a true man.

217
00:10:01,041 --> 00:10:02,416
You wanna be a true man?

218
00:10:02,500 --> 00:10:03,666
What does that even mean?

219
00:10:03,750 --> 00:10:05,583
[YUKIMURA] It means I want
to be a great man.

220
00:10:05,666 --> 00:10:06,750
What?

221
00:10:06,833 --> 00:10:08,708
You do realize
you're a girl, don't you?

222
00:10:08,791 --> 00:10:10,250
That is of no importance.

223
00:10:10,333 --> 00:10:13,875
True and genuine men can
transcend their birth gender.

224
00:10:13,958 --> 00:10:16,208
Have you just been let
out of an insane asylum?

225
00:10:16,291 --> 00:10:17,625
Cuz ya sound kinda crazy.

226
00:10:18,791 --> 00:10:19,958
[YUKIMURA]
Big Brother.

227
00:10:20,041 --> 00:10:21,458
May I slay that
villain, please?

228
00:10:21,541 --> 00:10:23,750
You may not slay
student council members!

229
00:10:23,833 --> 00:10:24,833
I'm sorry, Aoi.

230
00:10:24,916 --> 00:10:26,250
But will you excuse us
for a minute?

231
00:10:26,333 --> 00:10:27,125
Sure.

232
00:10:27,208 --> 00:10:28,708
If that's what you really want.

233
00:10:30,166 --> 00:10:31,458
So, tell me.

234
00:10:31,541 --> 00:10:33,375
Anything new at
the Neighbors Club?

235
00:10:33,458 --> 00:10:34,791
No.

236
00:10:34,875 --> 00:10:36,750
Sena is still totally engrossed
with those video games

237
00:10:36,833 --> 00:10:38,791
about making friends
with girls and stuff.

238
00:10:38,875 --> 00:10:41,166
Man, she just won't
give up on those, will she?

239
00:10:41,250 --> 00:10:42,666
How is everyone else doing?

240
00:10:42,750 --> 00:10:44,250
[YUKIMURA]
I'm not sure.

241
00:10:44,333 --> 00:10:47,041
Yozora and Rika haven't been to
the clubroom for a few days now.

242
00:10:47,125 --> 00:10:49,125
Maria comes by to have
a snack now and again,

243
00:10:49,208 --> 00:10:50,916
but after that, she leaves.

244
00:10:51,000 --> 00:10:52,875
[KODAKA] So you and
Sena are the only ones

245
00:10:52,958 --> 00:10:54,500
who are showing up anymore?

246
00:10:54,583 --> 00:10:55,208
[YUKIMURA]
Yes.

247
00:10:55,291 --> 00:10:57,291
We're it, I'm afraid.

248
00:10:57,375 --> 00:10:58,458
[KODAKA]
Oh, great.

249
00:10:58,541 --> 00:11:01,250
What am I supposed
to do about this?

250
00:11:01,333 --> 00:11:03,625
[YUKIMURA] Big Brother,
I can carry half of these.

251
00:11:03,708 --> 00:11:04,750
[KODAKA]
No, they're not heavy.

252
00:11:04,833 --> 00:11:06,041
I'm fine.

